    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Galveston</placeName>
                <date>19 June 1853</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dr Sir!</p>
            <p>your kind notice in your last Occident of my<lb/> elevation to the
                    <sic>mayority</sic> of this city, has<lb/> gratified me in one sense, as I never
                was<lb/> inclined to ride into public notoriety.</p>
            <p>I accepted the office not for the sake of S<add>?</add>,<lb/> but merely to thwart
                the Designs of a certain<lb/> Clique who by the by were preaching publicly<lb/> the
                Crusades against our Nation</p>
            <p>This is certainly an Evidence if our people<lb/> would only sustain their rights and
                    <sic>priviledges</sic><lb/> in this <add>?</add> country, and Demean<lb/>
                themselves <add>accordingly</add>! They can be elevated to any office<lb/> they
                aspire</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Truly your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">M Sungson<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
            <p><persName>Mrs S.</persName> sends her respects to you</p>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <ref target="Occident_PDFs/Occ_11_3.pdf">The above text refers to Occident
                        Volume 11 No. 3 page 188. Click here to view.</ref>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
